      <sentence>
        <infon key="n">2</infon>
        <offset>103</offset>
        <text>Climate change scenarios predict a doubling of the atmospheric CO2 concentration by the end of this century.
</text>
        <annotation id="T3">
          <infon key="brat-id">T3</infon>
          <infon key="type">Increase</infon>
          <infon key="brat-type">text-bound</infon>
          <location length="8" offset="138"/>
          <text>doubling</text>
        </annotation>
        <annotation id="T13">
          <infon key="brat-id">T13</infon>
          <infon key="type">Variable</infon>
          <infon key="brat-type">text-bound</infon>
          <location length="33" offset="150"/>
          <text>the atmospheric CO2 concentration</text>
        </annotation>
        <relation id="E3">
          <infon key="brat-id">E3</infon>
          <infon key="type">Increase</infon>
          <infon key="brat-type">event</infon>
          <node refid="T3" role="Increase"/>
          <node refid="T13" role="Theme"/>
        </relation>
      </sentence>
      <sentence>
        <infon key="n">3</infon>
        <offset>212</offset>
        <text>Yet, how rising CO2 will affect the species composition of aquatic microbial communities is still largely an open question.
</text>
        <annotation id="T4">
          <infon key="brat-id">T4</infon>
          <infon key="type">Increase</infon>
          <infon key="brat-type">text-bound</infon>
          <location length="6" offset="221"/>
          <text>rising</text>
        </annotation>
        <annotation id="T14">
          <infon key="brat-id">T14</infon>
          <infon key="type">Variable</infon>
          <infon key="brat-type">text-bound</infon>
          <location length="3" offset="228"/>
          <text>CO2</text>
        </annotation>
        <relation id="E4">
          <infon key="brat-id">E4</infon>
          <infon key="type">Increase</infon>
          <infon key="brat-type">event</infon>
          <node refid="T4" role="Increase"/>
          <node refid="T14" role="Theme"/>
        </relation>
      </sentence>
      <sentence>
        <infon key="n">4</infon>
        <offset>336</offset>
        <text>In this study, we develop a resource competition model to investigate competition for dissolved inorganic carbon in dense algal blooms.
</text>
      </sentence>
      <sentence>
        <infon key="n">5</infon>
        <offset>472</offset>
        <text>The model predicts how dynamic changes in carbon chemistry, pH and light conditions during bloom development feed back on competing phytoplankton species.
</text>
        <annotation id="T5">
          <infon key="brat-id">T5</infon>
          <infon key="type">Change</infon>
          <infon key="brat-type">text-bound</infon>
          <location length="7" offset="503"/>
          <text>changes</text>
        </annotation>
        <annotation id="T2">
          <infon key="brat-id">T2</infon>
          <infon key="type">Variable</infon>
          <infon key="brat-type">text-bound</infon>
          <location length="2" offset="532"/>
          <text>pH</text>
        </annotation>
        <relation id="E5">
          <infon key="brat-id">E5</infon>
          <infon key="type">Change</infon>
          <infon key="brat-type">event</infon>
          <node refid="T5" role="Change"/>
          <node refid="T2" role="Theme"/>
        </relation>
      </sentence>
      <sentence>
        <infon key="n">6</infon>
        <offset>627</offset>
        <text>We test the model predictions in chemostat experiments with monocultures and mixtures of a toxic and non-toxic strain of the freshwater cyanobacterium Microcystis aeruginosa.
</text>
      </sentence>
      <sentence>
        <infon key="n">7</infon>
        <offset>802</offset>
        <text>The toxic strain was able to reduce dissolved CO2 to lower concentrations than the non-toxic strain, and became dominant in competition at low CO2 levels.
</text>
        <annotation id="T7">
          <infon key="brat-id">T7</infon>
          <infon key="type">Decrease</infon>
          <infon key="brat-type">text-bound</infon>
          <location length="6" offset="831"/>
          <text>reduce</text>
        </annotation>
        <annotation id="T15">
          <infon key="brat-id">T15</infon>
          <infon key="type">Variable</infon>
          <infon key="brat-type">text-bound</infon>
          <location length="13" offset="838"/>
          <text>dissolved CO2</text>
        </annotation>
        <relation id="E7">
          <infon key="brat-id">E7</infon>
          <infon key="type">Decrease</infon>
          <infon key="brat-type">event</infon>
          <node refid="T7" role="Decrease"/>
          <node refid="T15" role="Theme"/>
        </relation>
      </sentence>
      <sentence>
        <infon key="n">8</infon>
        <offset>957</offset>
        <text>Conversely, the non-toxic strain could grow at lower light levels, and became dominant in competition at high CO2 levels but low light availability.
</text>
        <annotation id="T9">
          <infon key="brat-id">T9</infon>
          <infon key="type">Increase</infon>
          <infon key="brat-type">text-bound</infon>
          <location length="4" offset="996"/>
          <text>grow</text>
        </annotation>
        <annotation id="T10">
          <infon key="brat-id">T10</infon>
          <infon key="type">Decrease</infon>
          <infon key="brat-type">text-bound</infon>
          <location length="5" offset="1004"/>
          <text>lower</text>
        </annotation>
        <annotation id="T11">
          <infon key="brat-id">T11</infon>
          <infon key="type">Correlate</infon>
          <infon key="brat-type">text-bound</infon>
